<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-19470] Exchange body is null when using Mongodb changeStreams with update operation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-19470</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the mongodb component as a ChangeStreams consumer, the fullDocument is null for update operations. It&apos;s normal if we refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/changeStream/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;mongodb documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a temporary fix, you can use the object id to get the modified document with a route like this:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mongodb:mongo?consumerType=changeStreams....&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
.to(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mongodb:mongo?operation=findById&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The MongoDbChangeStreamsThread.initializeCursor() method should be changed to use the fullDocument option when creating the iterable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
